The paper deals with privacy and data protection in the context of network embeddings, which are commonly used in machine learning and data mining. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.SI (Social and Information Networks). The paper also involves machine learning techniques and classifiers, which suggests cs.LG (Machine Learning) as another likely category. The paper discusses privacy attacks, which could fall under cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). The paper also involves the analysis of network structures, which could fall under cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) or cs.DB (Databases).
